    "Body": " Product Designer Flipside Crypto - Boston, MA Quick Apply Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $96,000 - $140,000 a year Qualifications Figma SaaS User Research Google Docs InVision Full Job Description Design at Flipside: Flipside's mission is to enable blockchain ecosystems to live up to their full potential. At Flipside Crypto, product development is a collaborative effort between customer-facing teams, data science, engineering, and design. Reporting to our Lead Designer, you'll help to define, shape, and improve our identity as well as our products. We seek someone who cares deeply about understanding and building for customer needs, and is eager to learn the parts of our industry that may be unfamiliar. You will: Design systems and workflows that shape our user experience Constantly improve our customer facing marketing materials and website. Work in a highly collaborative fashion with the design, product, and data science teams Participate in design reviews and share your work regularly with the team Help determine how we craft user-friendly and user-focused experiences to delight our customers. Iterate on process and iron out implementation down to the pixel level. Help to establish, build, and maintain a unique, flexible library of shared components Assist in research activity to assess the efficacy of our system, tools, and process, as well as customer questions and needs. Improve workflows on individual products, onboarding, and analytic services. Drive towards a unified and world-class presence both inside and outside the organization. You may be fit for this role if you: Are familiar with all phases of the design process Have experience designing for responsive websites and complex dashboards Can reduce complex problems down to the right balance of flexibility, power, and ease of use You care about details and are excited to keep pushing your work until it is pixel-perfect Are skilled in explaining your work, process, and decisions to cross-functional stakeholders and crave feedback to help you produce your best work Enjoy utilizing user research and metrics to guide design decisions Are familiar with industry standard design tools like Sketch, Figma, Invision, and Abstract Are comfortable managing work in tools such as Clubhouse, Slack, Google Docs Have 1-2+ years of experience in a hands-on design role Experience designing for SaaS is a plus You should include these in your application: A link to your online portfolio Your CV or LinkedIn profile What it's like to work at Flipside Crypto: Just as we help clients understand and drive growth, we strive for the same as a team. We are a highly cross-functional team and view the diversity in backgrounds and abilities as key to making us better. We are a startup ourselves, and see our work as constantly in progress. We operate with open feedback, transparency, fairness, and fun. We value thoughtful discussion and knowledge-sharing among a diverse set of peers and colleagues. We want everyone to feel comfortable sharing their opinions, getting to the root of problems, and helping us all make better decisions. ", 
